<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Charter Medical Gets Clearance to Buy 30 Hospitals: The Federal Trade 
Commission gave Macon, Ga.-based Charter Medical Corp. permission to purchase 
30 of the 47 psychiatric hospitals it seeks to acquire from Santa Monica-based 
National Medical Enterprises Inc., the companies said. On May 13, the agency 
requested more information on the transaction under the Hart-Scott-Rodino Act. 
The companies said they are still responding to requests for further 
information on the 17 other sites. The request has delayed the closing of the 
$200-million transaction, which was announced March 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
