<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; FARMERS MARKET TO EXTEND FRIDAY HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The hours for the city's farmers market will be extended Friday to allow 
people who have daytime jobs to shop for fresh produce after work. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours will be from 2 to 7 p.m. Regular hours are from 2 to 6 p.m. But if 
extending the market for one extra hour is successful, it may be continued 
through the summer. 
</P>
<P>
 The market features 25 to 30 farmers who sell fresh fruits and vegetables. 
</P>
<P>
 The market is at the southwest corner of Main Street and Orange Avenue, three 
blocks north of the city's pier. 
</P>
<P>
 More information is available by calling Orange County Farm Bureau at (714) 
573-0374.DEBRA CANO 
</P>
