<TEXT>
<P>
 Because of some earlier colorful language used during an altercation with a 
game official, Jack Charlton, Ireland's coach, was forced by FIFA to watch 
Tuesday's game against Norway from the stands. 
</P>
<P>
 That didn't stop him from sending instructions to assistant coach Maurice 
Setters by telephone, however. 
</P>
