 "I watched the match from where the television cameras are, just to the right 
of the center line," Charlton said. "It was quite good up there. The only thing 
was, you're not in the presence of your players. So you pick the phone up and 
you tell Maurice what you want him to do and how to handle the situation. To 
Maurice's credit, he did everything exactly right today." 
