<TEXT>
<P>
 Football is an irresistible aphrodisiac, it seems, and a baby boom is expected 
in Ireland in nine months' time from couples carried away by watching 
Charlton's side in action. 
</P>
<P>
 In the aftermath of Ireland's first two World Cup matches, in Dublin up to 100 
women more than usual have taken the morning-after birth pill. 
</P>
