<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; SPOTLIGHT; GOOD FISHING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dutch goalkeeper Ed de Goey had an interesting way of expressing how much he 
liked the team's accommodations in Orlando. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the nose of the salmon," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Huh? 
</P>
<P>
 Said a translator: "That's a Dutch expression that means 'the best.' " HELENE 
ELLIOTT 
</P>
