FISHING REPORT: LAKE PERRIS DELIVERS SURPRISING BIG FISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lakes Castaic and Casitas in Los Angeles and Ventura County, respectively, are 
still producing most of the bass weighing more than 10 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
 But out in the sweltering heat of Riverside County, Lake Perris has been 
yielding a surprising number of big fish. For the second consecutive week, bass 
of 10 pounds or better have been caught, topped by a 13-pound 14-ounce lunker 
taken from Lake Perris on a plastic worm by Robert Pickell of Midway City. 
