 Woodland Hills East scored seven runs in the fourth inning en route to a 10-0 
victory over Granada Hills East in an American Legion District 20 game Tuesday 
at Kennedy High. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was called after five innings because of the mercy rule. 
</P>
<P>
 Dusty Cook pitched a two-hitter for Woodland Hills East. 
</P>
<P>
