<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CASITAS SPRINGS; BOY, 4, STARTS BLAZE, BURNS FAMILY 
DUPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 4-year-old Casitas Springs boy who was playing with fire started a blaze 
Tuesday afternoon that destroyed the rear end of his family's duplex, causing 
$60,000 in damage, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 No residents were hurt in the fire, which occurred in the 8800 block of Nye 
Road about 2:20 p.m., but Firefighter Mark Fisher was treated for heat 
exhaustion at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 The blaze was started by Trevor Allen, who was playing with an undisclosed 
fire source under his bed, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a thing with kids that age -- especially boys," Ventura County Fire 
Investigator Bill Hager said. "They're curious about fire." 
</P>
<P>
 Trevor's baby-sitter, Helena Maria Ortiz, 21, told firefighters that she saw 
flames between the bed and the wall. She grabbed the boy and ran out of the 
duplex, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors said they did not hear any smoke alarms before the blaze broke out. 
</P>
<P>
 Hager said fire officials will decide later whether to offer any counseling to 
Trevor. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
