<P>
 Simi Valley police Tuesday were searching for a man who held up a Vons 
supermarket clerk at gunpoint and then fled with several hundred dollars in 
cash. 
</P>
<P>
 The man entered the Vons market at 2204 Tapo St. about 11 p.m. Monday, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 He approached the cashier, brandished a gun and demanded money from the 
register, police said. 
</P>
