EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; FARMERS' MARKET TO MOVE ACROSS STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks Farmers' Market will move across the street starting July 7, 
with 60 produce and flower vendors setting up booths in the Village Square 
Center on Moorpark Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Displaced from Janss Mall because of construction, the farmers' market will 
move permanently to the center between Hillcrest and Brazil streets. 
</P>
<P>
 The market will retain its regular hours: 4 to 8 p.m. Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Because the new location is more visible and offers more parking, farmers' 
market manager Karen Wetzel predicted that sales would pick up after the move. 
"It's really exciting," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 But Wetzel noted that when the Ventura Farmers' Market moved in 1991, vendors 
lost many faithful customers. 
</P>
<P>
 Sales dropped 15% after the move and stayed depressed for as long as six 
months. STEPHANIE SIMON 
