<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; SCHOOL DISTRICT PICKS AGENCY TO RUN SEARCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The governing board of the Santa Ana Unified School District has chosen 
Educational Search Services to recruit a superintendent to replace Rudy M. 
Castruita, who will leave the district near the end of July. 
</P>
<P>
 The board voted 4 to 1 last week to award the $14,500 contract to the 
group.Trustees Robert W. Balen, Audrey Yamagata-Noji, Rosemarie Avila and Sal 
Mendoza supported the move. Trustee Tom Chaffee opposed it, board secretary 
Georgia Adams said. 
</P>
<P>
 Educational Search Services, which is run by the California School Boards 
Assn., has helped more than 100 school districts recruit new superintendents 
over the past few years, said Don Champlin, assistant superintendent for 
personnel services for the district. 
</P>
<P>
 The group and its chief consultant Richard Montgomery will be responsible for 
developing criteria to screen candidates, advertising for the job, performing 
reference checks and helping negotiate a contract with the winning candidate. 
</P>
<P>
 The superintendent oversees about 3,600 full-time and 500 part-time employees. 
The job pays $124,000 a year, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The search may take take about four months to complete, Champlin said. JON 
NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
