order to close down his two fast-food restaurants and take other action for his 
failure to pay $124,000 in back taxes, penalties and interest, Assistant U.S. 
Atty. Nathan J. Hochman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Chiang actually paid Pittner $3,400 in several installments before his arrest 
on April 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Chiang faces a maximum sentence of 75 years in prison and $1.25 million in 
fines. 
