<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; WOMAN SOUGHT IN ROBBERY AT MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are searching for a 32-year-old Marina del Rey woman who lured an 
unwitting man to her Burbank motel room, where two male acquaintances waited to 
rob him. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, a 22-year-old Hollywood man, was left naked and handcuffed on the 
floor after being robbed of $8,720 in belongings, including a $3,000 guitar, 
$2,430 in clothing, $2,000 worth of jewelry, a $500 gun and a $400 computerized 
organizer, Burbank police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "The dollar loss is great, but the type of occurrence where a young woman 
invites a guy to her motel room and male companions are waiting to rip him off 
is not that unusual," Police Sgt. Scott Wilson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man told police he met Sally Ann Wiliamsen at a bar last week, exchanged 
phone numbers with her and finally got an invitation to spend the night with 
her at the Buena Vista Motel, 2255 Buena Vista St. 
</P>
<P>
 When he reached the motel room about 3 a.m. Monday, the man was surprised by 
two men with semi-automatic pistols -- one waiting in the bathroom and the 
other sitting in a chair -- police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunmen, apparently knowing their victim was armed, asked whether he was 
carrying any weapons, police said. He replied by turning over his own gun: a 
small caliber handgun kept in a shoulder holster. 
</P>
<P>
 He was ordered to take off his clothes and lie on the floor as the gunmen 
searched his backpack, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Once they left, he telephoned for help. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
