<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; SOUTH CAROLINA; CITADEL ARGUES FOR WOMAN'S CREW CUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If Shannon Faulkner wants to be the first woman to march with The Citadel's 
all-male corps of cadets she should have to look like one, crew cut and all, 
the college told a judge. Her lawyers, however, said the requirement would be 
punitive and inconsistent with the way the military treats women. The 
state-supported military school in South Carolina originally accepted Faulkner 
but changed its mind when it discovered that she is a woman. U.S. District 
Judge C. Weston Houck will rule next month on her admittance. 
</P>
