<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; FLORIDA; DEPORTING OF FOREIGN CRIMINALS TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two dozen foreign criminals will be released from Florida prisons and handed 
over to federal authorities for deportation today, the governor and immigration 
authorities in Miami said.The deportations are the first scheduled under an 
unprecedented agreement between Gov. Lawton Chiles and the Justice Department. 
To make more room for violent criminals in Florida's crowded prisons, 
nonviolent prisoners who entered the United States illegally will have their 
sentences commuted if they agree to be deported. Immigration officials said 113 
prisoners from 16 countries have agreed. Many were serving time for drug 
crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
