</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dealing Down: New-car dealers in Southern California say they are starting to 
see some improvement after four years of recession -- but Auto Age Dealer 
Business magazine's annual listing of the nation's top 500 dealerships shows 
that the economic slump has taken its toll here. 
</P>
<P>
 California used to dominate the list -- in 1990 there were 104 dealerships 
from the Golden State among the top 500 dealers by gross sales.In the latest 
rankings, for 1993, there are just 79. 
</P>
<P>
 Car buyers put 13 Orange County dealers on the list, down from 17 in 1990. 
That decline tracks the industry's overall fortunes: There were 150 new-car 
dealers in Orange County in 1990, but the county Motor Car Dealers Assn. only 
counts 117 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
